body:
@cotedm I was hoping that we could convert the errors on the broker side. From a high level, my thought was that we need not necessarily expose the fact that group metadata is stored in a topic in the protocol since it is an implementation detail. We have code in `GroupMetadataManager` to convert produce errors to something nicer for the group protocol. See here: https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/coordinator/GroupMetadataManager.scala#L209. 

By the way, as I was looking over the same code, I noticed that the same error seems possible for OffsetCommit requests as well, so maybe we also need to convert those errors here: https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/trunk/core/src/main/scala/kafka/coordinator/GroupMetadataManager.scala#L307.

Also, should we go ahead and resolve KAFKA-3766 as a duplicate?
